46 PoseTracking::PoseTracking(const ros::NodeHandle& nh,
47  const planning_scene_monitor::PlanningSceneMonitorPtr& planning_scene_monitor)
48  : nh_(nh)
49  , planning_scene_monitor_(planning_scene_monitor)
50  , loop_rate_(DEFAULT_LOOP_RATE)
51  , transform_listener_(transform_buffer_)
52  , stop_requested_(false)
53  , angular_error_(boost::none)
54 {
55  readROSParams();
56 
57  robot_model_ = planning_scene_monitor_->getRobotModel();
58  joint_model_group_ = robot_model_->getJointModelGroup(move_group_name_);
59 
60  // Initialize PID controllers
61  initializePID(x_pid_config_, cartesian_position_pids_);
62  initializePID(y_pid_config_, cartesian_position_pids_);
63  initializePID(z_pid_config_, cartesian_position_pids_);
64  initializePID(angular_pid_config_, cartesian_orientation_pids_);
65 
66  // Use the C++ interface that Servo provides
67  servo_ = std::make_unique<moveit_servo::Servo>(nh_, planning_scene_monitor_);
68  servo_->start();
69 
70  // Connect to Servo ROS interfaces
71  target_pose_sub_ =
72  nh_.subscribe<geometry_msgs::PoseStamped>("target_pose", 1, &PoseTracking::targetPoseCallback, this);
73 
74  // Publish outgoing twist commands to the Servo object
75  twist_stamped_pub_ =
76  nh_.advertise<geometry_msgs::TwistStamped>(servo_->getParameters().cartesian_command_in_topic, 1);
77 }

79 PoseTrackingStatusCode PoseTracking::moveToPose(const Eigen::Vector3d& positional_tolerance,
80  const double angular_tolerance, const double target_pose_timeout)
81 {
82  // Reset stop requested flag before starting motions
83  stop_requested_ = false;
84  // Wait a bit for a target pose message to arrive.
85  // The target pose may get updated by new messages as the robot moves (in a callback function).
86  const ros::Time start_time = ros::Time::now();
87  while ((!haveRecentTargetPose(target_pose_timeout) || !haveRecentEndEffectorPose(target_pose_timeout)) &&
88  ((ros::Time::now() - start_time).toSec() < target_pose_timeout))
89  {
90  if (servo_->getCommandFrameTransform(command_frame_transform_))
91  {
92  command_frame_transform_stamp_ = ros::Time::now();
93  }
94  ros::Duration(0.001).sleep();
95  }
96 
97  if (!haveRecentTargetPose(target_pose_timeout))
98  {
99  ROS_ERROR_STREAM_NAMED(LOGNAME, "The target pose was not updated recently. Aborting.");
100  return PoseTrackingStatusCode::NO_RECENT_TARGET_POSE;
101  }
102 
103  // Continue sending PID controller output to Servo until one of the following conditions is met:
104  // - Goal tolerance is satisfied
105  // - Target pose becomes outdated
106  // - Command frame transform becomes outdated
107  // - Another thread requested a stop
108  while (ros::ok() && !satisfiesPoseTolerance(positional_tolerance, angular_tolerance))
109  {
110  // Attempt to update robot pose
111  if (servo_->getCommandFrameTransform(command_frame_transform_))
112  {
113  command_frame_transform_stamp_ = ros::Time::now();
114  }
115 
116  // Check that end-effector pose (command frame transform) is recent enough.
117  if (!haveRecentEndEffectorPose(target_pose_timeout))
118  {
119  ROS_ERROR_STREAM_NAMED(LOGNAME, "The end effector pose was not updated in time. Aborting.");
120  doPostMotionReset();
121  return PoseTrackingStatusCode::NO_RECENT_END_EFFECTOR_POSE;
122  }
123 
124  if (stop_requested_)
125  {
126  ROS_INFO_STREAM_NAMED(LOGNAME, "Halting servo motion, a stop was requested.");
127  doPostMotionReset();
128  return PoseTrackingStatusCode::STOP_REQUESTED;
129  }
130 
131  // Compute servo command from PID controller output and send it to the Servo object, for execution
132  twist_stamped_pub_.publish(calculateTwistCommand());
133 
134  if (!loop_rate_.sleep())
135  {
136  ROS_WARN_STREAM_THROTTLE_NAMED(1, LOGNAME, "Target control rate was missed");
137  }
138  }
139 
140  doPostMotionReset();
141  return PoseTrackingStatusCode::SUCCESS;
142 }

144 void PoseTracking::readROSParams()
145 {
146  // Optional parameter sub-namespace specified in the launch file. All other parameters will be read from this namespace.
147  std::string parameter_ns;
148  ros::param::get("~parameter_ns", parameter_ns);
149 
150  // If parameters have been loaded into sub-namespace within the node namespace, append the parameter namespace
151  // to load the parameters correctly.
152  ros::NodeHandle nh = parameter_ns.empty() ? nh_ : ros::NodeHandle(nh_, parameter_ns);
153 
154  // Wait for ROS parameters to load
155  ros::Time begin = ros::Time::now();
156  while (ros::ok() && !nh.hasParam("planning_frame") && ((ros::Time::now() - begin).toSec() < ROS_STARTUP_WAIT))
157  {
158  ROS_WARN_STREAM_NAMED(LOGNAME, "Waiting for parameter: "
159  << "planning_frame");
160  ros::Duration(0.1).sleep();
161  }
162 
163  std::size_t error = 0;
164 
165  error += !rosparam_shortcuts::get(LOGNAME, nh, "planning_frame", planning_frame_);
166  error += !rosparam_shortcuts::get(LOGNAME, nh, "move_group_name", move_group_name_);
167  if (!planning_scene_monitor_->getRobotModel()->hasJointModelGroup(move_group_name_))
168  {
169  ++error;
170  ROS_ERROR_STREAM_NAMED(LOGNAME, "Unable to find the specified joint model group: " << move_group_name_);
171  }
172 
173  double publish_period;
174  error += !rosparam_shortcuts::get(LOGNAME, nh, "publish_period", publish_period);
175  loop_rate_ = ros::Rate(1 / publish_period);
176 
177  x_pid_config_.dt = publish_period;
178  y_pid_config_.dt = publish_period;
179  z_pid_config_.dt = publish_period;
180  angular_pid_config_.dt = publish_period;
181 
182  double windup_limit;
183  error += !rosparam_shortcuts::get(LOGNAME, nh, "windup_limit", windup_limit);
184  x_pid_config_.windup_limit = windup_limit;
185  y_pid_config_.windup_limit = windup_limit;
186  z_pid_config_.windup_limit = windup_limit;
187  angular_pid_config_.windup_limit = windup_limit;
188 
189  error += !rosparam_shortcuts::get(LOGNAME, nh, "x_proportional_gain", x_pid_config_.k_p);
190  error += !rosparam_shortcuts::get(LOGNAME, nh, "y_proportional_gain", y_pid_config_.k_p);
191  error += !rosparam_shortcuts::get(LOGNAME, nh, "z_proportional_gain", z_pid_config_.k_p);
192  error += !rosparam_shortcuts::get(LOGNAME, nh, "x_integral_gain", x_pid_config_.k_i);
193  error += !rosparam_shortcuts::get(LOGNAME, nh, "y_integral_gain", y_pid_config_.k_i);
194  error += !rosparam_shortcuts::get(LOGNAME, nh, "z_integral_gain", z_pid_config_.k_i);
195  error += !rosparam_shortcuts::get(LOGNAME, nh, "x_derivative_gain", x_pid_config_.k_d);
196  error += !rosparam_shortcuts::get(LOGNAME, nh, "y_derivative_gain", y_pid_config_.k_d);
197  error += !rosparam_shortcuts::get(LOGNAME, nh, "z_derivative_gain", z_pid_config_.k_d);
198 
199  error += !rosparam_shortcuts::get(LOGNAME, nh, "angular_proportional_gain", angular_pid_config_.k_p);
200  error += !rosparam_shortcuts::get(LOGNAME, nh, "angular_integral_gain", angular_pid_config_.k_i);
201  error += !rosparam_shortcuts::get(LOGNAME, nh, "angular_derivative_gain", angular_pid_config_.k_d);
202 
203  rosparam_shortcuts::shutdownIfError(ros::this_node::getName(), error);
204 }

206 void PoseTracking::initializePID(const PIDConfig& pid_config, std::vector<control_toolbox::Pid>& pid_vector)

213 bool PoseTracking::haveRecentTargetPose(const double timespan)
214 {
215  std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lock(target_pose_mtx_);
216  return ((ros::Time::now() - target_pose_.header.stamp).toSec() < timespan);
217 }

219 bool PoseTracking::haveRecentEndEffectorPose(const double timespan)
220 {
221  return ((ros::Time::now() - command_frame_transform_stamp_).toSec() < timespan);
222 }

224 bool PoseTracking::satisfiesPoseTolerance(const Eigen::Vector3d& positional_tolerance, const double angular_tolerance)
225 {
226  std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lock(target_pose_mtx_);
227  double x_error = target_pose_.pose.position.x - command_frame_transform_.translation()(0);
228  double y_error = target_pose_.pose.position.y - command_frame_transform_.translation()(1);
229  double z_error = target_pose_.pose.position.z - command_frame_transform_.translation()(2);
230 
231  // If uninitialized, likely haven't received the target pose yet.
232  if (!angular_error_)
233  return false;
234 
235  return ((std::abs(x_error) < positional_tolerance(0)) && (std::abs(y_error) < positional_tolerance(1)) &&
236  (std::abs(z_error) < positional_tolerance(2)) && (std::abs(*angular_error_) < angular_tolerance));
237 }
238 
239 void PoseTracking::targetPoseCallback(const geometry_msgs::PoseStampedConstPtr& msg)
240 {
241  std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lock(target_pose_mtx_);
242  target_pose_ = *msg;
243 
244  // If the target pose is not defined in planning frame, transform the target pose.
245  if (target_pose_.header.frame_id != planning_frame_)
246  {
247  try
248  {
249  geometry_msgs::TransformStamped target_to_planning_frame = transform_buffer_.lookupTransform(
250  planning_frame_, target_pose_.header.frame_id, ros::Time(0), ros::Duration(0.1));
251  tf2::doTransform(target_pose_, target_pose_, target_to_planning_frame);
252 
253  // Prevent doTransform from copying a stamp of 0, which will cause the haveRecentTargetPose check to fail servo motions
254  target_pose_.header.stamp = ros::Time::now();
255  }
256  catch (const tf2::TransformException& ex)
257  {
258  ROS_WARN_STREAM_NAMED(LOGNAME, ex.what());
259  return;
260  }
261  }
262 }

264 geometry_msgs::TwistStampedConstPtr PoseTracking::calculateTwistCommand()
265 {
266  // use the shared pool to create a message more efficiently
267  auto msg = moveit::util::make_shared_from_pool<geometry_msgs::TwistStamped>();
268 
269  // Get twist components from PID controllers
270  geometry_msgs::Twist& twist = msg->twist;
271  Eigen::Quaterniond q_desired;
272 
273  // Scope mutex locking only to operations which require access to target pose.
274  {
275  std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lock(target_pose_mtx_);
276  msg->header.frame_id = target_pose_.header.frame_id;
277 
278  // Position
279  twist.linear.x = cartesian_position_pids_[0].computeCommand(
280  target_pose_.pose.position.x - command_frame_transform_.translation()(0), loop_rate_.expectedCycleTime());
281  twist.linear.y = cartesian_position_pids_[1].computeCommand(
282  target_pose_.pose.position.y - command_frame_transform_.translation()(1), loop_rate_.expectedCycleTime());
283  twist.linear.z = cartesian_position_pids_[2].computeCommand(
284  target_pose_.pose.position.z - command_frame_transform_.translation()(2), loop_rate_.expectedCycleTime());
285 
286  // Orientation algorithm:
287  // - Find the orientation error as a quaternion: q_error = q_desired * q_current ^ -1
288  // - Use the angle-axis PID controller to calculate an angular rate
289  // - Convert to angular velocity for the TwistStamped message
290  q_desired = Eigen::Quaterniond(target_pose_.pose.orientation.w, target_pose_.pose.orientation.x,
291  target_pose_.pose.orientation.y, target_pose_.pose.orientation.z);
292  }
293 
294  Eigen::Quaterniond q_current(command_frame_transform_.rotation());
295  Eigen::Quaterniond q_error = q_desired * q_current.inverse();
296 
297  // Convert axis-angle to angular velocity
298  Eigen::AngleAxisd axis_angle(q_error);
299  // Cache the angular error, for rotation tolerance checking
300  angular_error_ = axis_angle.angle();
301  double ang_vel_magnitude =
302  cartesian_orientation_pids_[0].computeCommand(*angular_error_, loop_rate_.expectedCycleTime());
303  twist.angular.x = ang_vel_magnitude * axis_angle.axis()[0];
304  twist.angular.y = ang_vel_magnitude * axis_angle.axis()[1];
305  twist.angular.z = ang_vel_magnitude * axis_angle.axis()[2];
306 
307  msg->header.stamp = ros::Time::now();
308 
309  return msg;
310 }

312 void PoseTracking::stopMotion()
313 {
314  stop_requested_ = true;
315 
316  // Send a 0 command to Servo to halt arm motion
317  auto msg = moveit::util::make_shared_from_pool<geometry_msgs::TwistStamped>();
318  {
319  std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lock(target_pose_mtx_);
320  msg->header.frame_id = target_pose_.header.frame_id;
321  }
322  msg->header.stamp = ros::Time::now();
323  twist_stamped_pub_.publish(msg);
324 }
325 
326 void PoseTracking::doPostMotionReset()
327 {
328  stopMotion();
329  stop_requested_ = false;
330  angular_error_ = boost::none;
331 
332  // Reset error integrals and previous errors of PID controllers
333  cartesian_position_pids_[0].reset();
334  cartesian_position_pids_[1].reset();
335  cartesian_position_pids_[2].reset();
336  cartesian_orientation_pids_[0].reset();
337 }

339 void PoseTracking::updatePIDConfig(const double x_proportional_gain, const double x_integral_gain,
340  const double x_derivative_gain, const double y_proportional_gain,
341  const double y_integral_gain, const double y_derivative_gain,
342  const double z_proportional_gain, const double z_integral_gain,
343  const double z_derivative_gain, const double angular_proportional_gain,
344  const double angular_integral_gain, const double angular_derivative_gain)
345 {
346  stopMotion();
347 
348  x_pid_config_.k_p = x_proportional_gain;
349  x_pid_config_.k_i = x_integral_gain;
350  x_pid_config_.k_d = x_derivative_gain;
351  y_pid_config_.k_p = y_proportional_gain;
352  y_pid_config_.k_i = y_integral_gain;
353  y_pid_config_.k_d = y_derivative_gain;
354  z_pid_config_.k_p = z_proportional_gain;
355  z_pid_config_.k_i = z_integral_gain;
356  z_pid_config_.k_d = z_derivative_gain;
357 
358  angular_pid_config_.k_p = angular_proportional_gain;
359  angular_pid_config_.k_i = angular_integral_gain;
360  angular_pid_config_.k_d = angular_derivative_gain;
361 
362  cartesian_position_pids_.clear();
363  cartesian_orientation_pids_.clear();
364  initializePID(x_pid_config_, cartesian_position_pids_);
365  initializePID(y_pid_config_, cartesian_position_pids_);
366  initializePID(z_pid_config_, cartesian_position_pids_);
367  initializePID(angular_pid_config_, cartesian_orientation_pids_);
368 
369  doPostMotionReset();
370 }

372 void PoseTracking::getPIDErrors(double& x_error, double& y_error, double& z_error, double& orientation_error)
373 {
374  double dummy1, dummy2;
375  cartesian_position_pids_.at(0).getCurrentPIDErrors(&x_error, &dummy1, &dummy2);
376  cartesian_position_pids_.at(1).getCurrentPIDErrors(&y_error, &dummy1, &dummy2);
377  cartesian_position_pids_.at(2).getCurrentPIDErrors(&z_error, &dummy1, &dummy2);
378  cartesian_orientation_pids_.at(0).getCurrentPIDErrors(&orientation_error, &dummy1, &dummy2);
379 }
